==English==
===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]] /'pɪgm'eliɒn/

===Adjective===
# Used as a title for someone of scientific importance, as in George Bernard Shaw's ''Pygmalion'' in which he sometimes refers to his main character (Henry Higgins) as Pygmalion Higgins.
# Bloody (only in 'not pygmalion likely'), from the sensational, and then scandalous, line 'not bloody likely' in George Bernard Shaw's play ''Pygmalion''.